              },
              "free_text": [
                " The McGill Synchrocyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deuteron beam was obtained in the external beam",
                "of the McGill Synchrocyclotron. The energy of the",
                "beam after extraction was 50 MeV. The beam energy was",
                "varied using beryllium degraders."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "It consists of 20 (or less) 12.5 mm diameter, 0.13 mm",
                "thick graphite discs which are coated on one side",
                "with target material. The target material was in the",
                "form of 233U02 and was deposited on each graphite",
                "disc with an average thickness of 0.8 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "OLMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experiments were performed using",
                "a pulsed beam mode. The bombardment and data",
                "collection times were chosen from a prior study of",
                "diffusion curves (yield vs. time) of Rb, Cs, and In",
                "produced with the beam burst. The typical fast",
                "components of the diffusion curves for Rb, In, and Cs",
                "ranged between 0.1 and 0.3 s. Optimum choice of data",
                "collection cycles, selected by an external clock,",
                "enable groups of data to be accumulated on the",
                "on-line PDP-15 mini-computer before, during, and",
                "after each beam burst. The isotopic mass distribution",
                "for each of Rb, In, and Cs could be obtained by",
                "subtracting the beam-off data from the beam-on data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " No details on sources of uncertainties."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The observed mass distributions were corrected for",
                "diffusion time, decays of short-lived radio isotopes,",
                "and sweep correction effects, for the determination",
                "of accurate values of relative yields."
              ]
            }
          ],
